Others: Jack Leiter, the Rangers' No. 4 prospect, pitched 5.1 innings, allowing 3 runs and striking out a career-high 6 batters.
Leiter's outing was a step in the right direction for him, as he continues to become more comfortable at the big league level.
Manager Bruce Bochy noted that Leiter's routine orientation has been beneficial, as being with the big league club has allowed him to establish a new routine.
